http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The national and local authorities are also investing \\u20ac1.4 billion (S$2.04 billion) in five projects designed to clean the water.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The weather remains the \\\"main risk\\\", acknowledges the Paris town hall, which fears \\\"exceptional rainfall\\\".\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996193765, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris town hall\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H\\u00f4tel_de_Ville,_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only back-up plan for the swimming is postponing the events by a few days.\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no solution to move the event, the triathlon and open water swimming will be held in the Seine next year,\\\" Tony Estanguet, Paris 2024 organising committee, said after the cancellations last August.\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2479, \"end\": 2484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999454303, \"rank\": 5.4559673758071064e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2497, \"end\": 2511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the athletes, these are the Olympics and dirty water is a constant risk in open-water competitions.\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of the test event in 2019 ahead of the Tokyo Olympics, swimmers protested against the quality of the water in Tokyo Bay.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the Rio Olympics in 2016, the polluted Guanabara Bay made headlines.\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2837, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0156774446144625e-19, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A glittering setting,\\\" Italian double world champion Gregorio Paltrinieri told Italian media in January.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2927, \"end\": 2934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.6183984955850332, \"rank\": 0.617034971576343, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gregorio Paltrinieri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\"}, {\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.6183984955850332, \"rank\": 0.617034971576343, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Even if the water is dirty, I would rather swim in an electric atmosphere in the centre of Paris than in an anonymous stretch of water.\\\"\